City of Chicago, Appellee, v. Hugh Early, Appellant.Gen. No. 24,332.

(Not to he reported in full.)

Appeal from the Municipal Court of Chicago; the Hon. Joseph Ha But, Judge, presiding.Heard in this court at the March term, 1918.Affirmed.Opinion filed March 25, 1918.

Statement of the Case.

Prosecution by the City of Chicago, plaintiff, against Hugh Early, defendant, for violation of an ordinance. Defendant appealed, but failed to file the record at the proper term. Appellee docketed the cause, filed a short record and moved to affirm the judgment of the Municipal Court.

This case is governed by the decision in City of Chicago v. Salmitsky, ante, p. 159.

No appearance for appellant.Harry B. Miller and Daniel Webster, for appellee. Mr. Presiding Justice Holdom

delivered the opinion of the court.
